    "order": 4
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1999_Solutions_1999s_page_003_2",
    "text": "B-1 The answer is 1/3. Let G be the point obtained by reflecting C about the line AB. Since LADC = *-®, we find that LBDE = * - 0 - LADC = 1-0 = LADC = П - LBDC = * - LBDG, so that E, D, G are collinear. Hence",
