    "text": "B-2 First solution: Suppose that P does not have n distinct roots; then it has a root of multiplicity at least 2, which we may assume is x = 0 without loss of generality. Let x be the greatest power of x dividing P(x), so that P(x) = x*R(x) with R(0) # 0; a simple computation yields",
