    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1999_Solutions_1999s_page_003_26",
    "text": "B-4 (based on work by Daniel Stronger) We make repeated use of the following fact: if f is a differentiable function on all of R, lim, >-∞ f(x) ≥ 0, and f'(x) > 0 for all * E R, then f(x) > 0 for all x E R. (Proof: if f(y) < 0 for some x, then f(x) < f(y) for all x < y since f' > 0, but then lim, --∞ f(x) ≤ f(y) < O.)",
